{{Quote|What could be better than sailing the spacelanes and boarding vessels! HA! It sounds like a great life! Well, you're missing out, I say!|[[Boyrake]], to a spacer|<ref name="SWG:Ac" />}}
The '''Canyon Corsairs''', also known as the '''Corsair Raiders''' or simply as the '''Corsairs''', were a group of [[Pirate/Legends|pirates]] active on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Lok/Legends|Lok]] and in the [[Karthakk system]] during the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]].

==Description==
{{Quote|They aren't a very friendly bunch so be careful!|[[Boyrake]], to a spacer|<ref name="SWG:Ac" />}}
The Canyon Corsairs were active in the [[Karthakk system]]. They were named after [[the Canyon]], an area of the [[Karthakk system]] that served as their home. The pirates were also present in other quadrants such as [[Nym's Hovel]], [[Voria's Ember]], the [[Censorious Tempest Nebula]] and the [[Corsairian Crescent]].<ref name="SCKS">{{SonyCite|url=en_US/players/content.vm?id=66849&resource=features|text=Star Chart: Karthakk System}}</ref> They were based on the planet Lok where they had built a [[Canyon Corsair's Stronghold|small stronghold]] out in the wilderness.<ref name="SWG:CCS" />

The Corsairs were a ruthless band of hooligans promising to wreck havoc on any passing civilian or vessel.<ref name="SCKS" /> The typical Canyon Corsair considered him- or herself above average vehicle pilots and was typically skilled in all sorts of vehicles such as [[Swoop/Legends|swoops]], [[Landspeeder/Legends|landspeeders]], and [[Starship/Legends|starships]]. Canyon Corsairs spent most of their time working on their vehicles, the parts for which they did not always acquire honestly.<ref name="CDAG">{{SonyCite|url=players/guides.vm?id=80112|text=CorSec Database A-G|int=CorSec Database A-G}}</ref> In space, Corsair pilots flew [[Z-95-AF4 Headhunter/Legends|Z-95-AF4 Headhunters]], [[Ixiyen-class fast attack craft|''Ixiyen''-class fast attack crafts]], [[M12-L Kimogila heavy fighter]]s and [[T-65 X-wing starfighter/Legends|T-65 X-wing starfighters]].<ref name="SWG:JtL" />

The Canyon Corsairs were enemies of the [[Blood Razors]] and [[Nym/Legends|Nym's]] [[Lok Revenants/Legends|Lok Revenants]].<ref name="FS">{{SonyCite|url=content.jsp?page=Faction%20Standings|text=Faction Standings}}</ref>

==History==
{{Quote|Help our shipments get through to Lok without being hijacked by those Canyon Corsairs.|[[Shamdon Kree]], to a pilot|<ref name="SWG:JtL" />}}
After the [[Battle of Yavin/Legends|Battle of Yavin]], the retired [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] [[Imperial Navy/Legends|Naval]] [[Captain/Legends|Captain]] [[Boyrake]] and the former [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel]] [[Spy/Legends|spy]] [[Talia v'laenya]] discovered the location of the Canyon Corsair's Stronghold on Lok.<ref name="SWG:Ac" /><ref name="SWG:Tv">{{SWGcite|exp=AED|type=herald|Talia v'laenya|Lok}}</ref>

In [[1 ABY/Legends|1 ABY]],<ref name="SWG_timeline">{{SWG_timeline}}</ref> the Corsairs hijacked several [[Valarian Syndicate|Valarian]] shipments transported to Nym's organization. [[Shamdon Kree]] therefore dispatched elite pilots from [[Talon Karrde]]'s [[Smugglers' Alliance|Smuggler Alliance]] to deal with the pirates. Many Corsairs were killed, including the pirate leader known as the [[Canyon Corsair Behemoth]].<ref name="SWG:JtL" />

